attributeList.attribute: Actin cytoskeleton-regulatory complex which is believed to be required for the internalization of endosomes during actin-coupled endocytosis. The complex links the site of endocytosis to the cell membrane-associated actin cytoskeleton, coordinating ARP2/3 stimulation at the later stages of endocytosis. Present in the late endocytic coat.

END3 and PAN1 appear to be constitutively bound. The inclusion of SLA1 in the complex appear to be dependent on the phosphorylation status of PAN1. phosphorylation of PAN1 terminates its ARP2/3 activation, disrupts its association with SLA1, and returns PAN1 to the cytosol.
